          <p>The School of Computer Science offers scholarships for students wishing to study a degree in a Computer Science subject. Scholarships are awarded to students who have, or who are expected to achieve excellent academic results.  Scholarships are available in the following levels of study:</p>

<h2>Undergraduate Scholarships</h2>

<p>We have a number of <a href="/admissions/undergraduate/scholarships">Undergraduate Scholarships</a> available for <a href="/admissions/undergraduate/home-scholarships">UK/EU</a> and <a href="/admissions/international/scholarships">international</a> students.</p>

<h2>Postgraduate Scholarships</h2>

<p>We have a number of scholarships available for Home/EU and international students at both <a href="/admissions/postgraduate-taught/scholarships">taught</a> and <a href="/admissions/postgraduate-research/scholarships">research</a> level.</p>

<h2>General University Fees and Funding Support</h2>

<p>The University of Birmingham has a Student Funding Office on hand to provide you with financial advice and support throughout your studies. We also offer a range of scholarships, grants and bursaries for undergraduate students, which we would advise you to explore. To talk to a member of staff regarding University fees and funding, please contact: <a href="tel:+441214147391">+44 (0)121 414 7391</a>, or make an online enquiry <a href="http://www.birmingham.ac.uk/undergraduate/support/moneyadvice/support.aspx">here</a>.</p>

